<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>2 Storey Luxury House – Engineering Cost & Materials (2026 PH)</title>

<style>
body{
margin:0;
font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
color:#e8f5e9;

/* ENGINEERING BLUEPRINT BACKGROUND */
background-color:#0f3d2e;
background-image:
linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.05) 1px, transparent 1px),
linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.05) 1px, transparent 1px);
background-size:40px 40px;
}

.container{
padding:40px;
}

h1,h2,h3{
color:#a5d6a7;
letter-spacing:1px;
}

.section{
margin-bottom:50px;
padding:25px;
background:rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
border:1px solid #2e7d32;
border-radius:10px;
}

table{
width:100%;
border-collapse:collapse;
margin-bottom:20px;
}

th,td{
border:1px solid #2e7d32;
padding:10px;
}

th{
background:#1b5e20;
color:#ffffff;
}

.total{
background:#2e7d32;
font-weight:bold;
color:#ffffff;
}

button{
background:#2e7d32;
color:white;
padding:10px 15px;
border:none;
border-radius:6px;
cursor:pointer;
}

button:hover{
background:#66bb6a;
color:#000;
}

input{
padding:8px;
margin:5px;
}

.result{
font-size:18px;
font-weight:bold;
margin-top:10px;
color:#a5d6a7;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>
<div class="container">

<h1>2 Storey Luxury House – Complete Engineering Breakdown (350 m²)</h1>

<div class="section">
<h2>1. COST PER SQUARE METER BASIS (2026 PH – High-End)</h2>
<p><strong>₱50,000 per m²</strong></p>
<p>350 m² × ₱50,000/m²</p>
<h3>Base Building Cost: ₱17,500,000</h3>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>2. TRADE COST DISTRIBUTION</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Trade</th><th>Allocation (%)</th><th>Cost (PHP)</th></tr>
<tr><td>Structural Works</td><td>28%</td><td>₱4,900,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Architectural Works</td><td>25%</td><td>₱4,375,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Electrical Works</td><td>10%</td><td>₱1,750,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Plumbing & Sanitary</td><td>8%</td><td>₱1,400,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>HVAC</td><td>7%</td><td>₱1,225,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Doors & Windows</td><td>8%</td><td>₱1,400,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Roofing & Waterproofing</td><td>6%</td><td>₱1,050,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Exterior Works</td><td>5%</td><td>₱875,000</td></tr>
<tr class="total"><td>Total</td><td>100%</td><td>₱17,500,000</td></tr>
</table>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>3. MATERIALS BREAKDOWN</h2>

<h3>Structural Materials</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Material</th><th>Quantity</th><th>Unit</th><th>Total Cost (PHP)</th></tr>
<tr><td>Cement</td><td>2,800</td><td>bags (40 kg)</td><td>₱798,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sand</td><td>220</td><td>m³</td><td>₱264,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Gravel</td><td>180</td><td>m³</td><td>₱252,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Reinforcing Steel Bars</td><td>28,000</td><td>kg</td><td>₱1,960,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Formworks</td><td>-</td><td>Lump Sum</td><td>₱450,000</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Electrical Materials</h3>
<table>
<tr><td>Wires & Conduits</td><td>₱650,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Main Distribution Panel</td><td>₱150,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Lighting Fixtures</td><td>₱480,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Switches & Receptacles</td><td>₱250,000</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Plumbing Materials</h3>
<table>
<tr><td>PPR & PVC Pipes</td><td>₱450,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sanitary Fixtures</td><td>₱550,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Shower & Mixer Sets</td><td>₱320,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Water Tank & Pump</td><td>₱180,000</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Flooring & Finishes</h3>
<table>
<tr><td>Porcelain Floor Tiles</td><td>₱850,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Engineered Wood Flooring</td><td>₱650,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Bathroom Wall & Floor Tiles</td><td>₱420,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Adhesives & Grout</td><td>₱150,000</td></tr>
</table>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>4. SWIMMING POOL CONSTRUCTION COST</h2>
<table>
<tr><td>Reinforced Concrete Shell</td><td>₱450,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Waterproofing System</td><td>₱180,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Mosaic Tile Finish</td><td>₱250,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Filtration & Pump System</td><td>₱300,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pool Deck Finish</td><td>₱300,000</td></tr>
<tr class="total"><td>Total Pool Cost</td><td>₱1,600,000</td></tr>
</table>
</div>

<!-- ✅ FIXED SECTION -->
<div class="section">
<h2>5. GRAND TOTAL PROJECT COST</h2>

<p>Building Construction (Labor Included): ₱17,500,000</p>
<p>Swimming Pool: ₱1,600,000</p>

<h3>Subtotal: ₱19,100,000</h3>
<p>Contingency (10%): ₱1,910,000</p>
<p>Contractor Profit (10%): ₱1,910,000</p>

<h1>Final Project Budget: ₱22,920,000</h1>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>6. COST CALCULATOR</h2>

<label>Floor Area (m²):</label>
<input type="number" id="sqm" value="350">

<label>Cost per m² (PHP):</label>
<input type="number" id="rate" value="50000">

<button onclick="computeCost()">Compute</button>

<div class="result" id="result"></div>
</div>

</div>

<script>
function computeCost(){
var sqm = document.getElementById("sqm").value;
var rate = document.getElementById("rate").value;
var total = sqm * rate;
document.getElementById("result").innerHTML =
"Estimated Construction Cost: ₱ " + Number(total).toLocaleString();
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
